{"format": "tiptap/v1", "updatedAt": "2026-06-22T11:04:40.345Z", "doc": {"type": "doc", "content": [{"type": "image", "attrs": {"src": "data:image/svg+xml;base64,", "alt": "Context Vector — concept overview"}}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "What Context Vector Is"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "context vector"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (also called \""}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "thought vector"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\") in Sequence-to-Sequence (Seq2Seq) models is a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "fixed-length numerical representation"}, {"type": "text", "text": " that summarizes the entire input sequence. It is the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "output of the encoder"}, {"type": "text", "text": " and serves as the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "input (initial state) for the decoder"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", acting as the bridge that passes learned information from encoder to decoder."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Why Context Vector Matters in Generative AI"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The context vector is critical because it:"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Role"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Impact"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Compresses entire input"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Captures the meaning of the whole input sequence in one vector"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Bridges encoder-decoder"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Passes learned information from encoder to decoder"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Enables variable lengths"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Allows input and output to have different lengths (e.g., 3 words → 5 words)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Generates output"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Decoder uses it to generate each element of the output sequence"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Without the context vector, the decoder would have no information about what the input sequence meant."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "How Context Vector Is Generated"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In Basic Seq2Seq (No Attention):"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Input Sequence: [x₁, x₂, x₃, ..., xₙ]\n\nEncoder RNN processes step-by-step:\n  Step 1: h₁ = f(U·x₁ + W·h₀)\n  Step 2: h₂ = f(U·x₂ + W·h₁)\n  ...\n  Step n: hₙ = f(U·xₙ + W·hₙ₋₁)\n  \nOutput: Context Vector = hₙ (final hidden state)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "For LSTM"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Context vector is typically the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "final hidden state "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "h_n"}}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": " and "}, {"type": "text", "text": "cell state "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "C_n"}}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The formula is:\n\\[\nc = \\text{Encoder}(x_1, x_2,..., x_n)\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "c"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " is the context vector, and usually "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "c = h_n"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " for LSTM."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "In Seq2Seq with Attention:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Input Sequence: [x₁, x₂, x₃, ..., xₙ]\n\nEncoder produces: [h₁, h₂, h₃, ..., hₙ] (all hidden states)\n\nAttention computes:\n  αᵢⱼ = attention weight for each hidden state\n  c = Σ(αᵢⱼ · hⱼ) (weighted sum)\n  \nOutput: Context Vector = weighted sum of all hidden states"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Formula"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n\\[\nc_i = \\sum_j (\\alpha"}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "italic"}], "text": "{ij} \\cdot h_j)\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Where "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "\\alpha_{ij}"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " are attention weights deciding which input parts are most relevant."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Characteristics"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Property"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Description"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Fixed length"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Same dimension regardless of input sequence length"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Learned representation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Specific to the task and model architecture (not just average of word embeddings)"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Compressed summary"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Contains all relevant information from input sequence"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Numerical vector"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "List of numbers representing the \"essence\" of the input"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The Information Bottleneck Problem"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The context vector is the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "bottleneck"}, {"type": "text", "text": " of the encoder-decoder architecture:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Input Sequence (variable length)\n  ↓\nEncoder (RNN/LSTM)\n  ↓\nContext Vector (fixed length, e.g., 512 numbers) ← BOTTLENECK\n  ↓\nDecoder (RNN/LSTM)\n  ↓\nOutput Sequence (variable length)"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "The problem"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": The entire input sequence must be compressed into a single fixed-length vector. This means:"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Long sequences may lose information"}, {"type": "text", "text": " (details get lost in compression)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Important words may be underrepresented"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Decoder can only \"see\" the compressed summary"}, {"type": "text", "text": ", not the original input"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Solution"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Attention mechanism allows decoder to look back at specific input words instead of relying solely on the compressed vector."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Context Vector Usage in Decoding"}]}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Without Attention:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Decoder receives: Context Vector c\n\nAt each decoding step t:\n  h_t = Decoder(y_{t-1}, h_{t-1}, c)\n  y_t = predict next token based on h_t\n  \nOutput: [y₁, y₂, y₃, ..., yₘ]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The decoder uses the context vector as its "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "initial hidden state"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":\n\\[\nh_0^{\\text{dec}} = h_n^{\\text{enc}}\n\\]"}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 3}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "With Attention:"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "yaml"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "At each decoding step t:\n  1. Compute attention weights αᵢⱼ for each encoder hidden state\n  2. Compute context vector c_t = Σ(αᵢⱼ · hⱼ)\n  3. Use c_t + h_{t-1} + y_{t-1} to predict y_t\n\nOutput: [y₁, y₂, y₃, ..., yₘ]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Attention creates a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "new context vector at each step"}, {"type": "text", "text": " based on what's relevant."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Example: Machine Translation"}]}, {"type": "codeBlock", "attrs": {"language": "text"}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Input (Arabic): [\"أنا\", \"أحب\", \"الذكاء\", \"التصنيع\"]\n                 (\"I\"  \"love\" \"AI\"    \"engineering\")\n\nEncoder processes:\n  Step 1: h₁ from \"أنا\"\n  Step 2: h₂ from \"أحب\"\n  Step 3: h₃ from \"الذكاء\"\n  Step 4: h₄ from \"التصنيع\"\n  \nContext Vector: c = h₄ (final hidden state)\n  = [0.23, -0.45, 0.78, ..., 0.12] (512 numbers representing \"I love AI engineering\")\n\nDecoder uses c to generate:\n  Step 1: c + start_token → \"I\"\n  Step 2: c + \"I\" → \"love\"\n  Step 3: c + \"love\" → \"AI\"\n  Step 4: c + \"AI\" → \"engineering\"\n  \nOutput (English): [\"I\", \"love\", \"AI\", \"engineering\"]"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The context vector captures the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "entire meaning"}, {"type": "text", "text": " of the Arabic sentence in 512 numbers."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefits of Context Vector"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Benefit"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Explanation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Fixed-size representation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Enables standard neural network operations"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Compresses information"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Captures semantic meaning of entire sequence"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Enables generation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Decoder uses it to generate output step-by-step"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Language-independent"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Works for any language or domain"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Trade-offs & Limitations"}]}, {"type": "table", "content": [{"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Limitation"}]}]}, {"type": "tableHeader", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Explanation"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Information bottleneck"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Must compress entire input into fixed size"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Loss of detail"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Long sequences may lose important information"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "No word-level access"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Decoder can't see specific words, only compressed summary"}]}]}]}, {"type": "tableRow", "content": [{"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "One vector for all"}]}]}, {"type": "tableCell", "attrs": {"colspan": 1, "rowspan": 1, "colwidth": null, "align": null}, "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Same vector used for all decoding steps (without attention)"}]}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Solution"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Attention allows decoder to access specific input words dynamically at each step."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Mental Model"}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Think of the context vector as a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "notebook summary"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Encoder"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = You reading a 10-page article and taking notes"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Context Vector"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = Your 1-page summary capturing all key points"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Decoder"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = Someone else reading your notes and explaining the article to another person"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The notes (context vector) must capture everything important, but some details might be lost in compression."}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Or think of it as a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "compressed ZIP file"}, {"type": "text", "text": ":"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Input sequence"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = A large folder of files"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Context vector"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = The compressed ZIP file (smaller, but contains everything)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Decoder"}, {"type": "text", "text": " = Extracting the ZIP file to get the original content"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The challenge is that if the ZIP is too small, some files get cut off."}]}, {"type": "horizontalRule"}, {"type": "heading", "attrs": {"level": 2}, "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "Key Takeaways"}]}, {"type": "bulletList", "content": [{"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Context vector"}, {"type": "text", "text": " is a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "fixed-length numerical summary"}, {"type": "text", "text": " of the entire input sequence"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Also called \"thought vector\""}, {"type": "text", "text": " because it captures the \"essence\" of the input"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Generated by encoder"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Typically the "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "final hidden state"}, {"type": "text", "text": " "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "h_n"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " (and cell state "}, {"type": "inlineMath", "attrs": {"latex": "C_n"}}, {"type": "text", "text": " for LSTM)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Acts as bridge"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Passes learned information from encoder to decoder"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Fixed length"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Same dimension regardless of input sequence length (e.g., always 512 numbers)"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Information bottleneck"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Entire input must be compressed into one vector, which may lose details"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "With attention"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Context vector becomes a "}, {"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "weighted sum"}, {"type": "text", "text": " of all encoder hidden states, not just the final one"}]}]}, {"type": "listItem", "content": [{"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "marks": [{"type": "bold"}], "text": "Critical for translation, summarization, chatbots"}, {"type": "text", "text": ": Allows decoder to generate output based on input meaning"}]}]}]}, {"type": "paragraph", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "The context vector is the core mechanism that enables Seq2Seq models to convert one sequence into another, especially when enhanced with attention mechanisms to overcome the information bottleneck."}]}]}}